text: Summary: The document contains a sample dataset for Ad Astra School, including structured student records, unstructured school information, exam schedules, fee structure, school rules, and a sample timetable for Class 10.

Facts and Numbers: Student records include Student ID (AA001-AA010), Name, Class (7B-10A), Subject (Mathematics, Science, English, Social Studies), Marks (56-94), Attendance % (76-97). Fee Structure: Annual Tuition Fee: I60,000, Exam Fee (per term): I2,000, Transport Fee (optional): I15,000 per year. Exam Schedule: Unit Test 1: July 15, Mid-Term Exams: September 10–15, Unit Test 2: December 5, Final Exams: March 1–10. Attendance below 75% is not permitted for final exams.

Knowledge Block - Student Records: The dataset includes student IDs, names, classes, subjects, marks, and attendance percentages for ten students at Ad Astra School.  The students are in classes 7B, 8A, 9A, 10A, and 10B and take subjects Mathematics, Science, English, and Social Studies. Marks range from 56 to 94, and attendance ranges from 76% to 97%.
Knowledge Block - Fee Structure: The annual tuition fee for Ad Astra School is I60,000. The exam fee is I2,000 per term.  The optional transport fee is I15,000 per year.
Knowledge Block - Exam Schedule: Ad Astra School's exam schedule includes Unit Test 1 on July 15, Mid-Term Exams from September 10–15, Unit Test 2 on December 5, and Final Exams from March 1–10.

Knowledge Block - School Rules: Ad Astra School prohibits attendance below 75% for final exams, strictly prohibits mobile phones on campus, requires students to wear the prescribed uniform at all times, and mandates respectful behavior towards staff and peers.

Knowledge Block - Sample Timetable (Class 10): A sample timetable for Class 10 at Ad Astra School is: 9:00–10:00 – Mathematics, 10:00–11:00 – Science, 11:15–12:15 – English, 12:15–1:00 – Lunch Break, 1:00–2:00 – Social Studies, 2:00–3:00 – Computer Science.
